'''''Conybeare's Textbook of Medicine''''' is a [[medical textbook]]. The first edition was published in 1929 and it reached its fifteenth edition in 1970, causing a reviewer to state the review was "superfluous".<ref>British Journal of General Practice 1970</ref> Another review stated it was "old-fashioned and readable...well written".<ref>Annals of Internal Medicine 1965</ref>

The doctor for whom the text is named is John Josias Conybeare, son of [[Frederick Cornwallis Conybeare]]. He was on the staff of [[Guy's Hospital]] from which he retired in 1953, and died in 1967.<ref>British Medical Journal 1967</ref>

